title: For Sale:  Ruger 10/22 Takedown LNIB
postcontent:
For sale is a LNIB Ruger 10/22 Take Down with a stainless finish that has never been fired. I have installed a Magpul single point sling on the left side as well as a Nodak Spud LLC - rear sight w/rail ($72) and a Nodak Spud LLC 10/22 front sight ($40). Also comes with 3-10 round magazines and a Magpul M3 single point sling.

Sturm, Ruger & Company, Inc. (NYSE: RGR) is proud to introduce the Ruger 10/22 Takedown™. Readily separated into two subassemblies, the Ruger 10/22 Takedown offers a convenient transport and storage option for the popular Ruger® 10/22®. As reliable and accurate as every 10/22, the Ruger 10/22 Takedown makes it even easier to keep America's favorite rimfire rifle by your side.
The barrel and forend of the Ruger 10/22 Takedown are easily separated from the action and buttstock by pushing a recessed lever, twisting the subassemblies, and pulling them apart. Reassembly is the reverse of takedown, and is quick and easy. The friction fit lockup of the assembly joint is simple to adjust, but will rarely need re-adjustment after the first assembly. The lockup is secure and repeatable, ensuring an accurate return to zero, even when receiver-mounted optics are used.

The Ruger 10/22 Takedown is shipped in a ballistic nylon backpack-style case that features internal sleeves which hold the subassemblies. External pockets with MOLLE webbing provide storage for magazines, ammunition, and other accessories. Multiple attachment points for the padded, single shoulder strap offer different carrying options.

The 4.67-pound Ruger 10/22 Takedown is 37" long when assembled; each subassembly is less than 20 1/4" long when disassembled. Utilizing the standard 10/22 action and ten round rotary magazine (one magazine is provided), the Ruger 10/22 Takedown offers legendary 10/22 reliability in a compact and portable package.

For more information on the new Ruger 10/22 Takedown, or to learn more about the extensive line of award winning Ruger firearms, visit Ruger.com or Facebook.com/Ruger. To find accessories for the Ruger 10/22 Takedown, like the 25-round Ruger BX-25® magazine

title: For Sale:  WINCHESTER M1917 American Enfield, P17
postcontent:
For sale a really nice WWI Winchester US Model of 1917 (Pattern 17 Enfield), S/N 2263664, chambered for 30-06 Springfield. (The American Enfield.) A military collector in great condition! 

The stock is rock solid with no cracks and the expected handling marks.  It does have some cartouches behind the trigger guard, behind the lower band, and a very faint “RAP” on the left side.  The stock tip is marked “R”.

The metal finish and condition are great, and the receiver finish is outstanding. The only thing to mention is some VERY light pitting on the barrel, just behind the front sight. 

Behind the front sight the barrel is marked with a “E”, a flaming cannonball ordinance mark and the date code 12-18. This is fitting since the rifle was manufactured in May 1918.  

The action is nice. The bore seems to have some light pitting, and is a little dark, but the rifling is very strong. The bolt is the correct “Nickel Steel” stamped “W” bolt with all matching “W” parts.  

The bayonet lug/upper band is stamped “R” with an eagle proof.   Almost all the parts are marked with the “W” for Winchester and display the eagle proof.  

As I stated, the serial number on the receiver is 2636444, which by the majority of expert opinions indicates it was produced in May of 1918 [from 261,023 to 302,650]. (Experts disagree on exact production figures, but two published estimates of total production for all manufacturers- Winchester, Remington & Eddystone- as of November 1918 are 2,202,429 and 2,267,888.)  That makes this rifle having been produced and probably used during WWI.  

The rifle will come with a 1917 dated and maker marked M1907 sling and a nickel buttstock cleaning kit and oiler.  The sling is in very nice shape and is solid.  It has some cracking but as I stated, it is solid.  The oiler comes with the pullthrough and wisk brush.  All parts are in excellent shape.  The leather bumper and oiler bushing are in excellent shape.  Not all rotted out.

This rifle is not a lend lease and does not bear any foreign stamps This rifle is NOT import marked.

Winchester M1917’s are the rarest of the M1917’s.  Get one for your American War rifle collection while you can.  

Buyer is responsible for insuring that the item can be legally received. Do not buy if unable to meet this requirement. Sale will not be honored without this requirement. Buyer responsible for shipping cost and receiving transfer fees. Shipping cost will be $50.00, which includes insurance, to the lower 47 only. No shipment to CA, AK, HI and outside USA. Shipment by FEDEX to an FFL or C&R that has supplied a current copy of their license to seller before shipment. [No exceptions!] Payment to be by USPS Money Order only, sent by Certified Mail, and received before shipment will be made. Payment to include shipping cost if not a local pick-up. If payment is not received within 10-days of purchase, then transaction is voided, and item will be re-listed. Buyer responsible to ask questions before buying. Item offered “as-is”. No returns permitted. No warranties expressed or implied. By buying, the buyer agrees to hold seller harmless against damages, injury and death caused by item listed. SAFETY NOTICE: Sold as a collectible.  All firearms should be inspected by a qualified gunsmith if purchased other than as a collectible.

title: For Sale:  Galil 5.56 assault rifle, piston, 17 mags, folding, quad rail
postcontent:
Galil Golani 5.56/.223 with metal folding stock (no wobble). Rubber cheek weld attached to folding stock (removable). UTG quad rail with scope mount installed, quad rail covers included. Original foregrip included (not shown in pictures). Bipod stud mounted in quad rail. Folding forward pistol grip with storage compartment (composite). Bayonet lug. Flip up night sights present, but no glow left in tritium tubes. A new Israeli extractor and extractor spring were installed after purchase. The serial number starts with GAL and the ejector lug and receiver look great, good feed ramp. There have been between 350 and 500 rounds fired through the rifle since I purchased it new. Chromed bore is in fantastic shape. Shoots brass or steel case ammo and ejects both no problem.

This rifle is a combination of an AR-15 and an AK-47. The receiver is milled and the folding stock is very solid and locks up tight, made from steel tubing and a cast aluminum butt section. This rifle has a chromed gas piston and a right side charging handle, that can be charged with the left hand also as it is vertically oriented. The rifle is much more accurate than the typical AK-47 type design. Chrome lined barrel. The front sight hood is a full circle, so it is easy to line up with the ar style flip 2 size peep rear sights. There are flip up night sights but the tritium does not glow, the night sights can be replaced by new mepro sights from Optics Planet for about $80.

The magazines are all in very good shape and are metal, not plastic. There are (12) 35 round magazines. There are (5) 12 round magazines-purchased new (unused).  

CDNN is selling the 35 round magazines for $70 each plus shipping, that's over $1200 in magazines alone for 17 mags! The UTG quad rail/scope mount was $100.  So you are paying only $700 for the rifle, I paid more.

Price is $2000 cash, firm on price!
